    <!--Hair Type Descriptions-->
    <string name="hair_description">
        <![CDATA[
        <b>Hair Type 1: Straight</b> <br>
            1A. Stick-straight. <br>
            1B. Straight but with a slight body wave adding some volume. <br>
            1C. Straight with body wave and one or two visible S-waves (e.g. at nape of neck or temples). <br>
        <br>

        <b>Hair Type 2: Wavy</b> <br>
            2A. Loose with stretched S-waves throughout. <br>
            2B. Shorter with more distinct S-waves (resembling e.g. braided damp hair). <br>
            2C. Distinct S-waves, some spiral curling. <br>
        <br>

        <b>Hair Type 3: Curly</b> <br>
            3A. Big, loose spiral curls. <br>
            3B. Bouncy ringlets. <br>
            3C. Tight corkscrews. <br>
        <br>

        <b>Hair Type 4: Kinky</b> <br>
            4A. Tightly coiled S-curls. <br>
            4B. Z-patterned (tightly coiled, sharply angled) <br>
            4C. Mostly Z-patterned (tightly kinked, less definition)
         <br>
         <br>

         FIA hair typing system
        ]]>
